Sentencas: The effect of reactively sintered Mn1.5Co1.5O4 (MCO) coatings on the development of surface microstructure for Haynes 230 (H230) oxidized in air at 800 degrees C has been studied using a combination of thermo-gravimetric analysis and electron microscopy techniques.
Titulo: The effect of Mn1.5Co1.5O4 coatings on the development of near surface microstructure for Haynes 230 oxidized at 800 °C in air

Titulo: The effect of Mn1.5Co1.5O4 coatings on the development of near surface microstructure for Haynes 230 oxidized at 800 °C in air

Sentencas: For the MCO-coated H230, the reduction step of the reactive sintering process converts the MCO coating to a mixture of Co and MnO with a thin Cr-rich oxide layer at the interface with the alloy substrate.
Titulo: The effect of Mn1.5Co1.5O4 coatings on the development of near surface microstructure for Haynes 230 oxidized at 800 °C in air

Sentencas: Following the re-oxidation step, there is a 200 nm chromia layer and a 400 nm cubic spinel reaction layer (RL) between the alloy and the MCO.
